    "body": "My proposal would be: \r\n\r\n1. Start checking words using [our list](https://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/52cdcf8f0f1127f5ee694f39086a9e4df54174e6/extkeys/mnemonic.go#L97) right after this input is not active and show this warning if at least one word is wrong. \r\n<img width=\"491\" alt=\"screenshot 2018-08-09 10 34 06\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6559881/43892894-2e0160b6-9bc5-11e8-98e6-dfcfd6a3e598.png\">\r\n\r\n2. If a user decides to proceed she will get this\r\n<img width=\"489\" alt=\"screenshot 2018-08-09 11 26 13\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6559881/43893531-3175ec42-9bc7-11e8-8382-8bcaf150ab7c.png\">\r\n\r\nThere is some possibility to meet people that not using standard words, but let's assume that they know what they are doing and keep the flow above since it's still possible to recover an account.\r\n\r\nPlease check the copy @obi2020  ",
